  "comment_text": {
    "snp3.1:5.1": "This is the only passage in the suttas where Bimbisāra appears in person. He does, however, feature quite frequently in the Vinaya. ",
    "snp3.1:6.2": "<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Suci</i> here refers to his appearance, as agreed by the commentary, so “pure” is not very useful. ",
    "snp3.1:11.2": "Reading <i lang='pi' translate='no'>tato</i>. ",
    "snp3.1:17.3": "Cp. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/ja542/en/sujato#176.3'>Ja 542:176.3</a>. ",
    "snp3.1:18.4": "",
    "snp3.1:19.1": "Buddhist tradition holds that the Buddha’s solar ancestry was shared with Bimbisāra. "
  },
