  "root_text": {
    "snp3.1:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 3.1 ",
    "snp3.1:0.2": "Pabbajjāsutta ",
    "snp3.1:1.1": "“Pabbajjaṁ kittayissāmi, ",
    "snp3.1:1.2": "yathā pabbaji cakkhumā; ",
    "snp3.1:1.3": "Yathā vīmaṁsamāno so, ",
    "snp3.1:1.4": "pabbajjaṁ samarocayi. ",
    "snp3.1:2.1": "Sambādhoyaṁ gharāvāso, ",
    "snp3.1:2.2": "rajassāyatanaṁ iti; ",
    "snp3.1:2.3": "Abbhokāsova pabbajjā, ",
    "snp3.1:2.4": "iti disvāna pabbaji. ",
    "snp3.1:3.1": "Pabbajitvāna kāyena, ",
    "snp3.1:3.2": "pāpakammaṁ vivajjayi; ",
    "snp3.1:3.3": "Vacīduccaritaṁ hitvā, ",
    "snp3.1:3.4": "ājīvaṁ parisodhayi. ",
    "snp3.1:4.1": "Agamā rājagahaṁ buddho, ",
    "snp3.1:4.2": "magadhānaṁ giribbajaṁ; ",
    "snp3.1:4.3": "Piṇḍāya abhihāresi, ",
    "snp3.1:4.4": "ākiṇṇavaralakkhaṇo”. ",
    "snp3.1:5.1": "Tamaddasā bimbisāro, ",
    "snp3.1:5.2": "pāsādasmiṁ patiṭṭhito; ",
    "snp3.1:5.3": "Disvā lakkhaṇasampannaṁ, ",
    "snp3.1:5.4": "imamatthaṁ abhāsatha. ",
    "snp3.1:6.1": "“Imaṁ bhonto nisāmetha, ",
    "snp3.1:6.2": "abhirūpo brahā suci; ",
    "snp3.1:6.3": "Caraṇena ca sampanno, ",
    "snp3.1:6.4": "yugamattañca pekkhati. ",
    "snp3.1:7.1": "Okkhittacakkhu satimā, ",
    "snp3.1:7.2": "nāyaṁ nīcakulāmiva; ",
    "snp3.1:7.3": "Rājadūtābhidhāvantu, ",
    "snp3.1:7.4": "kuhiṁ bhikkhu gamissati”. ",
    "snp3.1:8.1": "Te pesitā rājadūtā, ",
    "snp3.1:8.2": "piṭṭhito anubandhisuṁ; ",
    "snp3.1:8.3": "Kuhiṁ gamissati bhikkhu, ",
    "snp3.1:8.4": "kattha vāso bhavissati. ",
    "snp3.1:9.1": "Sapadānaṁ caramāno, ",
    "snp3.1:9.2": "guttadvāro susaṁvuto; ",
    "snp3.1:9.3": "Khippaṁ pattaṁ apūresi, ",
    "snp3.1:9.4": "sampajāno paṭissato. ",
    "snp3.1:10.1": "Piṇḍacāraṁ caritvāna, ",
    "snp3.1:10.2": "Nikkhamma nagarā muni; ",
    "snp3.1:10.3": "Paṇḍavaṁ abhihāresi, ",
    "snp3.1:10.4": "Ettha vāso bhavissati. ",
    "snp3.1:11.1": "Disvāna vāsūpagataṁ, ",
    "snp3.1:11.2": "Tayo dūtā upāvisuṁ; ",
    "snp3.1:11.3": "Tesu ekova āgantvā, ",
    "snp3.1:11.4": "Rājino paṭivedayi. ",
    "snp3.1:12.1": "“Esa bhikkhu mahārāja, ",
    "snp3.1:12.2": "Paṇḍavassa puratthato; ",
    "snp3.1:12.3": "Nisinno byagghusabhova, ",
    "snp3.1:12.4": "Sīhova girigabbhare”. ",
    "snp3.1:13.1": "Sutvāna dūtavacanaṁ, ",
    "snp3.1:13.2": "Bhaddayānena khattiyo; ",
    "snp3.1:13.3": "Taramānarūpo niyyāsi, ",
    "snp3.1:13.4": "Yena paṇḍavapabbato. ",
    "snp3.1:14.1": "Sa yānabhūmiṁ yāyitvā, ",
    "snp3.1:14.2": "Yānā oruyha khattiyo; ",
    "snp3.1:14.3": "Pattiko upasaṅkamma, ",
    "snp3.1:14.4": "Āsajja naṁ upāvisi. ",
    "snp3.1:15.1": "Nisajja rājā sammodi, ",
    "snp3.1:15.2": "Kathaṁ sāraṇīyaṁ tato; ",
    "snp3.1:15.3": "Kathaṁ so vītisāretvā, ",
    "snp3.1:15.4": "Imamatthaṁ abhāsatha. ",
    "snp3.1:16.1": "“Yuvā ca daharo cāsi, ",
    "snp3.1:16.2": "Paṭhamuppattiko susu; ",
    "snp3.1:16.3": "Vaṇṇārohena sampanno, ",
    "snp3.1:16.4": "Jātimā viya khattiyo. ",
    "snp3.1:17.1": "Sobhayanto anīkaggaṁ, ",
    "snp3.1:17.2": "Nāgasaṅghapurakkhato; ",
    "snp3.1:17.3": "Dadāmi bhoge bhuñjassu, ",
    "snp3.1:17.4": "Jātiṁ akkhāhi pucchito”. ",
    "snp3.1:18.1": "“Ujuṁ janapado rāja, ",
    "snp3.1:18.2": "Himavantassa passato; ",
    "snp3.1:18.3": "Dhanaviriyena sampanno, ",
    "snp3.1:18.4": "Kosalesu niketino. ",
    "snp3.1:19.1": "Ādiccā nāma gottena, ",
    "snp3.1:19.2": "Sākiyā nāma jātiyā; ",
    "snp3.1:19.3": "Tamhā kulā pabbajitomhi, ",
    "snp3.1:19.4": "Na kāme abhipatthayaṁ. ",
    "snp3.1:20.1": "Kāmesvādīnavaṁ disvā, ",
    "snp3.1:20.2": "Nekkhammaṁ daṭṭhu khemato; ",
    "snp3.1:20.3": "Padhānāya gamissāmi, ",
    "snp3.1:20.4": "Ettha me rañjatī mano”ti. ",
    "snp3.1:20.5": "Pabbajjāsuttaṁ paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp3.1:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 3.1 ",
    "snp3.1:0.2": "Going Forth ",
    "snp3.1:1.1": "“I shall extol going forth ",
    "snp3.1:1.2": "with the example of the Clear-eyed One, ",
    "snp3.1:1.3": "the course of inquiry that led to ",
    "snp3.1:1.4": "his choice to go forth. ",
    "snp3.1:2.1": "‘This life at home is cramped, ",
    "snp3.1:2.2": "a realm of dirt.’ ",
    "snp3.1:2.3": "‘The life of one gone forth is like an open space.’ ",
    "snp3.1:2.4": "Seeing this, he went forth. ",
    "snp3.1:3.1": "Having gone forth, he shunned ",
    "snp3.1:3.2": "bad deeds of body. ",
    "snp3.1:3.3": "And leaving verbal misconduct behind, ",
    "snp3.1:3.4": "he purified his livelihood. ",
    "snp3.1:4.1": "The Buddha went to Rājagaha, ",
    "snp3.1:4.2": "the Mountainfold of the Magadhans. ",
    "snp3.1:4.3": "He betook himself for alms, ",
    "snp3.1:4.4": "replete with excellent marks. ",
    "snp3.1:5.1": "Bimbisāra saw him ",
    "snp3.1:5.2": "while standing atop his longhouse. ",
    "snp3.1:5.3": "Noticing that he was endowed with marks, ",
    "snp3.1:5.4": "he said the following: ",
    "snp3.1:6.1": "‘Pay heed, sirs, to this one, ",
    "snp3.1:6.2": "handsome, majestic, radiant; ",
    "snp3.1:6.3": "accomplished in deportment, ",
    "snp3.1:6.4": "he looks just a plough’s length in front. ",
    "snp3.1:7.1": "Eyes downcast, mindful, ",
    "snp3.1:7.2": "unlike one from a low family. ",
    "snp3.1:7.3": "Let the king’s messengers run out, ",
    "snp3.1:7.4": "and find where the mendicant will go.’ ",
    "snp3.1:8.1": "The messengers sent out ",
    "snp3.1:8.2": "followed right behind, thinking ",
    "snp3.1:8.3": "‘Where will the mendicant go? ",
    "snp3.1:8.4": "Where shall he find a place to stay?’ ",
    "snp3.1:9.1": "Wandering indiscriminately for alms, ",
    "snp3.1:9.2": "sense doors guarded and well restrained, ",
    "snp3.1:9.3": "his bowl was quickly filled, ",
    "snp3.1:9.4": "aware and mindful. ",
    "snp3.1:10.1": "Having wandered for alms, ",
    "snp3.1:10.2": "the sage left the city. ",
    "snp3.1:10.3": "He betook himself to Mount Paṇḍava, ",
    "snp3.1:10.4": "thinking, ‘Here is the place I shall stay.’ ",
    "snp3.1:11.1": "Seeing that he had arrived at a place to stay, ",
    "snp3.1:11.2": "the messengers withdrew nearby, ",
    "snp3.1:11.3": "but one of them returned ",
    "snp3.1:11.4": "to inform the king. ",
    "snp3.1:12.1": "‘Great king, the mendicant ",
    "snp3.1:12.2": "is on the east flank of Mount Paṇḍava. ",
    "snp3.1:12.3": "There he sits, like a tiger or a bull, ",
    "snp3.1:12.4": "like a lion in a mountain cave.’ ",
    "snp3.1:13.1": "Hearing the messenger’s report, ",
    "snp3.1:13.2": "the aristocrat set out ",
    "snp3.1:13.3": "hurriedly in his fine chariot ",
    "snp3.1:13.4": "towards Mount Paṇḍava. ",
    "snp3.1:14.1": "He went as far as vehicles could go, ",
    "snp3.1:14.2": "then dismounted from his chariot, ",
    "snp3.1:14.3": "approached on foot, ",
    "snp3.1:14.4": "and reaching him, drew near. ",
    "snp3.1:15.1": "Seated, the king greeted him ",
    "snp3.1:15.2": "and made polite conversation. ",
    "snp3.1:15.3": "When the courtesies were over, ",
    "snp3.1:15.4": "he said the following: ",
    "snp3.1:16.1": "‘You are young, just a youth, ",
    "snp3.1:16.2": "a lad in the prime of life. ",
    "snp3.1:16.3": "You are endowed with beauty and stature, ",
    "snp3.1:16.4": "like an aristocrat of good birth ",
    "snp3.1:17.1": "in glory at the army’s head, ",
    "snp3.1:17.2": "surrounded by a troop of elephants. ",
    "snp3.1:17.3": "I offer you pleasures—enjoy them! ",
    "snp3.1:17.4": "But please tell me of your birth.’ ",
    "snp3.1:18.1": "‘Up north, O King, ",
    "snp3.1:18.2": "on the slopes of the Himalayas, ",
    "snp3.1:18.3": "full of wealth and strength, lies the land ",
    "snp3.1:18.4": "of one whose abode is among the Kosalans. ",
    "snp3.1:19.1": "Their clan is named for the Sun, ",
    "snp3.1:19.2": "they are Sakyans by birth. ",
    "snp3.1:19.3": "I have gone forth from that family—",
    "snp3.1:19.4": "I do not yearn for sensual pleasure. ",
    "snp3.1:20.1": "Seeing the danger in sensual pleasures, ",
    "snp3.1:20.2": "seeing renunciation as sanctuary, ",
    "snp3.1:20.3": "I shall go on to strive; ",
    "snp3.1:20.4": "that is where my mind delights.’” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp3.1:11.2": "Tayo → tato (bj, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp3.1:11.3": "ekova → eko va dūto (bj); eko ca dūto (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp3.1:12.2": "puratthato → purakkhato (bj, sya-all, mr) ",
    "snp3.1:16.2": "Paṭhamuppattiko → paṭhamuppatito (bj); paṭhamuppattito (sya-all) ",
    "snp3.1:18.4": "Kosalesu → kosalassa (sya-all, mr) ",
    "snp3.1:19.1": "Ādiccā → ādicco (mr) ",
    "snp3.1:19.2": "Sākiyā → sākiyo (mr) "
  },
